---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Tools" description="Interactive GxP reference tools: ALCOA+ self-assessment, GAMP 5 category decision aid, 483 response checklist, validation deliverable selector, and self-audit checklists.">
 <div class="page-header">
 <div class="page-label">Reference Tools</div>
 <h1>Tools</h1>
 <p>
 Interactive reference tools and self-audit checklists for GxP quality work.
 Everything on this page runs in your browser. No login, no data sent anywhere.
 </p>
 </div>

 <!-- Audit Guides -->
 <div class="section-divider">
 <div class="page-label">Audit Guides</div>
 <h2 class="section-heading">Self-Audit Checklists</h2>
 <p class="section-desc">Detailed structured checklists to evaluate compliance programs, designed to find what FDA and EMA inspectors find.</p>
 </div>

 <div class="audit-grid">
 <a href="/articles/di-self-audit-checklist" class="audit-card">
 <div class="audit-icon" style="color:#4f8ef7">DI</div>
 <div class="audit-body">
 <div class="audit-title">Data Integrity Self-Audit</div>
 <div class="audit-desc">5-layer DI compliance audit: infrastructure controls, system configuration, procedural controls, work practice forensics, and culture indicators. Structured around FDA, MHRA, WHO, and PIC/S DI expectations.</div>
 <div class="audit-meta">Advanced · Data Integrity</div>
 </div>
 </a>
 <a href="/articles/csv-csa-audit-checklist" class="audit-card">
 <div class="audit-icon" style="color:#34d399">CSV</div>
 <div class="audit-body">
 <div class="audit-title">CSV / CSA Program Self-Audit</div>
 <div class="audit-desc">Evaluate your computer system validation program: system inventory, GAMP category assignments, validation documentation quality, traceability, supplier assessment, change control, and periodic review. Aligned with GAMP 5 Second Edition and FDA CSA final guidance (Feb 2026).</div>
 <div class="audit-meta">Advanced · CSV &amp; CSA</div>
 </div>
 </a>
 <a href="/articles/equipment-qualification-audit-checklist" class="audit-card">
 <div class="audit-icon" style="color:#fbbf24">EQ</div>
 <div class="audit-body">
 <div class="audit-title">Equipment Qualification Audit</div>
 <div class="audit-desc">Full lifecycle qualification audit for analytical instruments and manufacturing equipment: DQ, IQ, OQ, PQ, calibration, maintenance, periodic review, and change control. References USP &lt;1058&gt;, EU Annex 15, and ISPE C&amp;Q Baseline Guide.</div>
 <div class="audit-meta">Intermediate · Equipment Qualification</div>
 </div>
 </a>
 <a href="/articles/qms-self-audit-checklist" class="audit-card">
 <div class="audit-icon" style="color:#f87171">QMS</div>
 <div class="audit-body">
 <div class="audit-title">QMS Self-Audit</div>
 <div class="audit-desc">Complete quality management system audit: document control, deviation management, CAPA quality and effectiveness, change control, training, supplier qualification, internal audits, and quality metrics. Aligned with ICH Q10 and FDA/EMA inspection expectations.</div>
 <div class="audit-meta">Intermediate · Quality Assurance</div>
 </div>
 </a>
 </div>

 <!-- Interactive Reference Checklists -->
 <div class="section-divider">
 <div class="page-label">Reference Tools</div>
 <h2 class="section-heading">Interactive Quick-Reference</h2>
 <p class="section-desc">Client-side reference tools for common GxP assessments. Nothing is sent anywhere, these run in your browser.</p>
 </div>

 <div class="checklists-grid">

 <!-- ALCOA+ Self-Assessment -->
 <div class="checklist-card" id="alcoa-card">
 <div class="checklist-header">
 <h3>ALCOA+ Self-Assessment</h3>
 <span class="checklist-count" id="alcoa-count">0 / 9</span>
 </div>
 <p class="checklist-desc">Evaluate a GxP record or system against all nine ALCOA+ principles. Check each principle only if your current controls fully satisfy it.</p>
 <div class="checklist-items" id="alcoa-items">
 <label class="cl-item"><input type="checkbox" data-group="alcoa" /><span class="cl-label"><strong>Attributable</strong>, Every entry can be traced to the person who made it. Individual accounts, no shared logins, signatures tied to individuals.</span></label>
 <label class="cl-item"><input type="checkbox" data-group="alcoa" /><span class="cl-label"><strong>Legible</strong>, Records are readable and permanently recorded. No pencil, no whitespace over corrections, no degraded ink or media.</span></label>
 <label class="cl-item"><input type="checkbox" data-group="alcoa" /><span class="cl-label"><strong>Contemporaneous</strong>, Recorded at the time the activity occurs. No backdating, no transcription from scratch paper, no post-hoc reconstruction.</span></label>
 <label class="cl-item"><input type="checkbox" data-group="alcoa" /><span class="cl-label"><strong>Original</strong>, The first capture of data is preserved. Raw data is retained; processed results do not overwrite originals.</span></label>
 <label class="cl-item"><input type="checkbox" data-group="alcoa" /><span class="cl-label"><strong>Accurate</strong>, Records reflect what actually happened. No manipulation of values, integration parameters, or reportable results.</span></label>
 <label class="cl-item"><input type="checkbox" data-group="alcoa" /><span class="cl-label"><strong>Complete</strong>, All data is included, including invalidated runs and OOS results. Nothing is selectively omitted.</span></label>
 <label class="cl-item"><input type="checkbox" data-group="alcoa" /><span class="cl-label"><strong>Consistent</strong>, Dates, times, and sequences are internally consistent and match across independent systems.</span></label>
 <label class="cl-item"><input type="checkbox" data-group="alcoa" /><span class="cl-label"><strong>Enduring</strong>, Records are stored in a durable format with defined retention periods and tested recovery procedures.</span></label>
 <label class="cl-item"><input type="checkbox" data-group="alcoa" /><span class="cl-label"><strong>Available</strong>, Records can be retrieved and presented in human-readable form throughout the retention period, including to regulators.</span></label>
 </div>
 <div class="checklist-progress">
 <div class="progress-bar"><div class="progress-fill" id="alcoa-fill" style="width:0%"></div></div>
 <span class="progress-label" id="alcoa-label">Not assessed</span>
 </div>
 </div>

 <!-- GAMP Category Decision Aid -->
 <div class="checklist-card" id="gamp-card">
 <div class="checklist-header">
 <h3>GAMP 5 Category Decision Aid</h3>
 <span class="checklist-result" id="gamp-result"></span>
 </div>
 <p class="checklist-desc">Answer questions to determine the GAMP 5 software category for a system under evaluation. Based on GAMP 5 Second Edition (2022).</p>
 <div class="gamp-questions">
 <div class="gamp-q" id="gamp-q1">
 <div class="gamp-q-text">Is this infrastructure software (OS, middleware, database engine, network services) that is not GxP-specific?</div>
 <div class="gamp-btns">
 <button class="gamp-btn" onclick="gampAnswer(1,'yes')">Yes</button>
 <button class="gamp-btn" onclick="gampAnswer(1,'no')">No</button>
 </div>
 </div>
 <div class="gamp-q hidden" id="gamp-q2">
 <div class="gamp-q-text">Is this COTS software used without configuration (non-configurable, used as-delivered)?</div>
 <div class="gamp-btns">
 <button class="gamp-btn" onclick="gampAnswer(2,'yes')">Yes</button>
 <button class="gamp-btn" onclick="gampAnswer(2,'no')">No</button>
 </div>
 </div>
 <div class="gamp-q hidden" id="gamp-q3">
 <div class="gamp-q-text">Is this COTS software configured to meet business requirements (workflow setup, report templates, access roles)?</div>
 <div class="gamp-btns">
 <button class="gamp-btn" onclick="gampAnswer(3,'yes')">Yes</button>
 <button class="gamp-btn" onclick="gampAnswer(3,'no')">No</button>
 </div>
 </div>
 <div class="gamp-answer hidden" id="gamp-cat1">
 <div class="gamp-cat cat1">Category 1, Infrastructure Software</div>
 <div class="gamp-cat-desc">Operating systems, DBMS, network services, and similar infrastructure. Validation activities focus on qualification of the installation environment and vendor support documentation. Supplier audits and patch management controls apply.</div>
 <button class="gamp-reset" onclick="gampReset()">Start over</button>
 </div>
 <div class="gamp-answer hidden" id="gamp-cat3">
 <div class="gamp-cat cat3">Category 3, Non-Configured Software</div>
 <div class="gamp-cat-desc">COTS software used as-delivered (instrument firmware, embedded controllers). Testing focuses on operational qualification of the supplied functionality. Vendor documentation review and supplier assessment are primary activities.</div>
 <button class="gamp-reset" onclick="gampReset()">Start over</button>
 </div>
 <div class="gamp-answer hidden" id="gamp-cat4">
 <div class="gamp-cat cat4">Category 4, Configured Software</div>
 <div class="gamp-cat-desc">COTS applications configured to meet requirements (LIMS, ELN, MES, QMS). IQ/OQ/PQ applies. Testing scope covers configured functionality. Configuration specifications and test scripts required. Change control governs configuration changes post-validation.</div>
 <button class="gamp-reset" onclick="gampReset()">Start over</button>
 </div>
 <div class="gamp-answer hidden" id="gamp-cat5">
 <div class="gamp-cat cat5">Category 5, Custom Software</div>
 <div class="gamp-cat-desc">Custom-developed or heavily customized applications. Highest validation rigor, full software development lifecycle controls, code review, unit/integration/system testing, and comprehensive documentation. SDLC must be defined and controlled.</div>
 <button class="gamp-reset" onclick="gampReset()">Start over</button>
 </div>
 </div>
 </div>

 <!-- 483 Response Checklist -->
 <div class="checklist-card" id="fda483-card">
 <div class="checklist-header">
 <h3>483 Response Completeness Check</h3>
 <span class="checklist-count" id="fda483-count">0 / 10</span>
 </div>
 <p class="checklist-desc">Before submitting a 483 response, verify each element is present and substantive. Check only items that are genuinely complete, not just drafts.</p>
 <div class="checklist-items" id="fda483-items">
 <label class="cl-item"><input type="checkbox" data-group="fda483" /><span class="cl-label"><strong>Acknowledgment</strong>, Each observation is addressed individually with a clear statement of agreement or disagreement.</span></label>
 <label class="cl-item"><input type="checkbox" data-group="fda483" /><span class="cl-label"><strong>Root cause analysis</strong>, Goes beyond the symptom to identify the underlying system failure (procedure gap, training gap, oversight gap, system design gap).</span></label>
 <label class="cl-item"><input type="checkbox" data-group="fda483" /><span class="cl-label"><strong>Immediate correction</strong>, Specific action taken to fix the observed condition. Completed before submission if possible.</span></label>
 <label class="cl-item"><input type="checkbox" data-group="fda483" /><span class="cl-label"><strong>Systemic CAPA</strong>, Preventive action addresses not just the cited instance but all similar situations across the site.</span></label>
 <label class="cl-item"><input type="checkbox" data-group="fda483" /><span class="cl-label"><strong>Specific timelines</strong>, Each action has a specific completion date. No vague language ("in the coming months").</span></label>
 <label class="cl-item"><input type="checkbox" data-group="fda483" /><span class="cl-label"><strong>Evidence attached</strong>, Completed actions are supported by evidence (SOPs, training records, validation documentation).</span></label>
 <label class="cl-item"><input type="checkbox" data-group="fda483" /><span class="cl-label"><strong>Scope assessment</strong>, Response addresses whether similar issues exist in other systems, products, or sites beyond what was directly cited.</span></label>
 <label class="cl-item"><input type="checkbox" data-group="fda483" /><span class="cl-label"><strong>Data integrity retrospective</strong>, If applicable: historical data affected by the finding has been assessed for impact on prior quality decisions.</span></label>
 <label class="cl-item"><input type="checkbox" data-group="fda483" /><span class="cl-label"><strong>Effectiveness monitoring</strong>, Plan is in place to verify that corrective actions are working (not just implemented).</span></label>
 <label class="cl-item"><input type="checkbox" data-group="fda483" /><span class="cl-label"><strong>Senior management acknowledgment</strong>, Response reflects management understanding of the issue and organizational commitment to corrective action.</span></label>
 </div>
 <div class="checklist-progress">
 <div class="progress-bar"><div class="progress-fill" id="fda483-fill" style="width:0%"></div></div>
 <span class="progress-label" id="fda483-label">Not assessed</span>
 </div>
 </div>

 <!-- Validation Deliverable Selector -->
 <div class="checklist-card" id="vd-card">
 <div class="checklist-header">
 <h3>Validation Deliverable Selector</h3>
 <span class="checklist-result" id="vd-result"></span>
 </div>
 <p class="checklist-desc">Select validation type to see required and recommended deliverables. Based on GAMP 5 Second Edition and FDA/EMA expectations.</p>
 <div class="vd-selector">
 <div class="vd-type-btns">
 <button class="vd-type-btn active" onclick="selectVDType('csv', this)">Computer System (CSV)</button>
 <button class="vd-type-btn" onclick="selectVDType('equipment', this)">Equipment / Instrument</button>
 <button class="vd-type-btn" onclick="selectVDType('process', this)">Process Validation</button>
 <button class="vd-type-btn" onclick="selectVDType('cleaning', this)">Cleaning Validation</button>
 </div>
 <div class="vd-list" id="vd-content">
 <!-- populated by JS -->
 </div>
 </div>
 </div>

 </div>
</Layout>

<script is:inline>
 // ── ALCOA+ and 483 progress bars ──────────────────────────────────────────
 function updateChecklistProgress(group, total) {
 var checked = document.querySelectorAll('input[data-group="' + group + '"]:checked').length;
 var fill = document.getElementById(group + '-fill');
 var countEl = document.getElementById(group + '-count');
 var labelEl = document.getElementById(group + '-label');
 if (!fill) return;
 var pct = Math.round((checked / total) * 100);
 fill.style.width = pct + '%';
 if (countEl) countEl.textContent = checked + ' / ' + total;
 if (labelEl) {
 if (checked === 0) labelEl.textContent = 'Not assessed';
 else if (checked === total) labelEl.textContent = 'All principles satisfied';
 else labelEl.textContent = pct + '% — ' + (total - checked) + ' gap(s) remain';
 }
 fill.style.background = checked === total ? '#34d399' : checked >= total * 0.7 ? '#4f8ef7' : '#f87171';
 }

 document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function () {
 document.querySelectorAll('input[data-group="alcoa"]').forEach(function (cb) {
 cb.addEventListener('change', function () { updateChecklistProgress('alcoa', 9); });
 });
 document.querySelectorAll('input[data-group="fda483"]').forEach(function (cb) {
 cb.addEventListener('change', function () { updateChecklistProgress('fda483', 10); });
 });
 renderVD('csv');
 });

 // ── GAMP Decision Aid ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 function gampAnswer(q, answer) {
 document.getElementById('gamp-q' + q).classList.add('hidden');
 if (q === 1) {
 if (answer === 'yes') { document.getElementById('gamp-cat1').classList.remove('hidden'); }
 else { document.getElementById('gamp-q2').classList.remove('hidden'); }
 } else if (q === 2) {
 if (answer === 'yes') { document.getElementById('gamp-cat3').classList.remove('hidden'); }
 else { document.getElementById('gamp-q3').classList.remove('hidden'); }
 } else if (q === 3) {
 if (answer === 'yes') { document.getElementById('gamp-cat4').classList.remove('hidden'); }
 else { document.getElementById('gamp-cat5').classList.remove('hidden'); }
 }
 }

 function gampReset() {
 ['gamp-q2','gamp-q3','gamp-cat1','gamp-cat3','gamp-cat4','gamp-cat5'].forEach(function (id) {
 document.getElementById(id).classList.add('hidden');
 });
 document.getElementById('gamp-q1').classList.remove('hidden');
 }

 // ── Validation Deliverables ───────────────────────────────────────────────
 var vdData = {
 csv: {
 required: ['Validation Plan / Master Validation Plan','User Requirements Specification (URS)','Functional Requirements Specification (FRS)','System Design Specification (SDS)','Installation Qualification (IQ)','Operational Qualification (OQ)','Performance Qualification (PQ)','Traceability Matrix (URS to Test Scripts)','Validation Summary Report','SOPs for system use and administration'],
 recommended: ['Supplier Assessment / Audit Report','Hardware and Software Design Review','Risk Assessment (system-level, GAMP appendix B)','Data Migration Validation (if applicable)','Periodic Review SOP and schedule','User Acceptance Testing (UAT) documentation'],
 },
 equipment: {
 required: ['Instrument Qualification Plan','User Requirements Specification (URS)','Installation Qualification (IQ)','Operational Qualification (OQ)','Performance Qualification (PQ)','Maintenance and calibration SOPs','Requalification trigger criteria (documented)'],
 recommended: ['Supplier / vendor documentation review','Design Qualification (DQ) for custom equipment','Preventive maintenance records integration','Risk assessment per USP 1058','Analytical Instrument Classification (AIC) decision'],
 },
 process: {
 required: ['Process Validation Protocol (PPQ stage 3)','Process Design summary (stage 1 data)','Process Performance Qualification (PPQ) report','Continued Process Verification (CPV) plan','Statistical process control criteria','Linkage to batch record and specifications'],
 recommended: ['Design of Experiments (DoE) data package','Process risk assessment (FMEA)','Scale-up / tech transfer summary','Site-specific contamination control strategy','Annual Product Review integration plan'],
 },
 cleaning: {
 required: ['Cleaning Validation Protocol','Acceptable Residue Limits (ARL) calculations','Swab and rinse recovery validation data','Worst-case product/equipment matrix','Cleaning Validation Report','Cleaning SOP and associated training records'],
 recommended: ['Visual inspection limits justification','Analytical method validation for residue testing','Hold time studies (dirty and clean)','Product grouping / bracketing rationale','Annual revalidation trigger criteria'],
 },
 };

 function renderVD(type) {
 var data = vdData[type];
 var container = document.getElementById('vd-content');
 if (!container || !data) return;
 container.innerHTML =
 '<div class="vd-section">' +
 '<div class="vd-section-title required-label">Required Deliverables</div>' +
 '<ul class="vd-list-items">' + data.required.map(function (d) { return '<li class="vd-item req">' + d + '</li>'; }).join('') + '</ul>' +
 '</div>' +
 '<div class="vd-section">' +
 '<div class="vd-section-title recommended-label">Recommended / Risk-Based</div>' +
 '<ul class="vd-list-items">' + data.recommended.map(function (d) { return '<li class="vd-item rec">' + d + '</li>'; }).join('') + '</ul>' +
 '</div>';
 }

 function selectVDType(type, btn) {
 document.querySelectorAll('.vd-type-btn').forEach(function (b) { b.classList.remove('active'); });
 btn.classList.add('active');
 renderVD(type);
 }
</script>

<style>
 .page-header {
 margin-bottom: 3rem;
 padding-bottom: 2rem;
 border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
 }

 .page-label {
 font-size: 0.72rem;
 font-family: var(--mono);
 color: var(--accent);
 text-transform: uppercase;
 letter-spacing: 0.1em;
 font-weight: 700;
 margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
 }

 .page-header h1 { font-size: 2.25rem; letter-spacing: -0.03em; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
 .page-header > p { color: var(--muted-light); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }

 /* ── Audit Guides ── */
 .audit-grid {
 display: grid;
 grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(340px, 1fr));
 gap: 1rem;
 margin-top: 1.5rem;
 }

 .audit-card {
 display: flex;
 gap: 1rem;
 align-items: flex-start;
 background: var(--surface);
 border: 1px solid var(--border);
 border-radius: 14px;
 padding: 1.5rem;
 text-decoration: none;
 transition: border-color 0.2s, transform 0.2s;
 }

 .audit-card:hover {
 border-color: var(--accent);
 transform: translateY(-2px);
 }

 .audit-icon {
 font-size: 0.7rem;
 font-family: var(--mono);
 font-weight: 800;
 letter-spacing: 0.05em;
 padding: 0.4rem 0.55rem;
 border-radius: 6px;
 background: var(--surface2);
 border: 1px solid var(--border);
 flex-shrink: 0;
 margin-top: 0.1rem;
 }

 .audit-body { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.4rem; }

 .audit-title {
 font-size: 0.95rem;
 font-weight: 600;
 color: var(--text);
 line-height: 1.3;
 }

 .audit-desc {
 font-size: 0.8rem;
 color: var(--muted-light);
 line-height: 1.6;
 }

 .audit-meta {
 font-size: 0.68rem;
 font-family: var(--mono);
 color: var(--muted);
 margin-top: 0.2rem;
 }

 /* ── Checklist section ── */
 .section-divider {
 margin: 4rem 0 2rem;
 padding-top: 3rem;
 border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
 }

 .section-heading {
 font-size: 1.5rem;
 letter-spacing: -0.03em;
 margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
 }

 .section-desc {
 color: var(--muted);
 font-size: 0.875rem;
 margin-bottom: 0;
 }

 .checklists-grid {
 display: grid;
 grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(420px, 1fr));
 gap: 1.25rem;
 margin-top: 1.5rem;
 }

 .checklist-card {
 background: var(--surface);
 border: 1px solid var(--border);
 border-radius: 14px;
 padding: 1.75rem;
 display: flex;
 flex-direction: column;
 gap: 1rem;
 }

 .checklist-header {
 display: flex;
 align-items: center;
 justify-content: space-between;
 gap: 1rem;
 }

 .checklist-header h3 {
 font-size: 1rem;
 font-weight: 600;
 color: var(--text);
 }

 .checklist-count, .checklist-result {
 font-size: 0.72rem;
 font-family: var(--mono);
 color: var(--muted);
 white-space: nowrap;
 }

 .checklist-desc {
 font-size: 0.825rem;
 color: var(--muted);
 line-height: 1.6;
 margin: 0;
 }

 .checklist-items {
 display: flex;
 flex-direction: column;
 gap: 0.5rem;
 }

 .cl-item {
 display: flex;
 align-items: flex-start;
 gap: 0.6rem;
 cursor: pointer;
 padding: 0.6rem 0.75rem;
 border-radius: 7px;
 border: 1px solid transparent;
 transition: border-color 0.15s, background 0.15s;
 }

 .cl-item:hover { border-color: var(--border); background: var(--surface2); }

 .cl-item input[type="checkbox"] {
 margin-top: 0.15rem;
 accent-color: var(--accent);
 flex-shrink: 0;
 width: 14px;
 height: 14px;
 }

 .cl-label {
 font-size: 0.8rem;
 color: var(--muted-light);
 line-height: 1.55;
 }

 .cl-label strong { color: var(--text); }

 .checklist-progress {
 display: flex;
 flex-direction: column;
 gap: 0.4rem;
 }

 .progress-bar {
 height: 4px;
 background: var(--surface2);
 border-radius: 99px;
 overflow: hidden;
 }

 .progress-fill {
 height: 100%;
 background: var(--accent);
 border-radius: 99px;
 transition: width 0.3s, background 0.3s;
 }

 .progress-label {
 font-size: 0.72rem;
 font-family: var(--mono);
 color: var(--muted);
 }

 /* GAMP decision aid */
 .gamp-questions { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; }

 .gamp-q { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.6rem; }
 .gamp-q-text { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted-light); line-height: 1.55; }
 .gamp-btns { display: flex; gap: 0.5rem; }

 .gamp-btn {
 font-size: 0.8rem;
 font-family: var(--mono);
 padding: 0.35rem 0.9rem;
 border: 1px solid var(--border);
 border-radius: 6px;
 background: var(--surface2);
 color: var(--muted-light);
 cursor: pointer;
 transition: border-color 0.15s, color 0.15s;
 }

 .gamp-btn:hover { border-color: var(--accent); color: var(--text); }

 .gamp-answer { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; }

 .gamp-cat {
 font-size: 0.875rem;
 font-weight: 700;
 padding: 0.5rem 0.85rem;
 border-radius: 7px;
 }

 .cat1 { background: rgba(148,163,184,0.1); color: #94a3b8; border-left: 3px solid #94a3b8; }
 .cat3 { background: rgba(251,191,36,0.1); color: #fbbf24; border-left: 3px solid #fbbf24; }
 .cat4 { background: rgba(79,142,247,0.1); color: #4f8ef7; border-left: 3px solid #4f8ef7; }
 .cat5 { background: rgba(167,139,250,0.1); color: #a78bfa; border-left: 3px solid #a78bfa; }

 .gamp-cat-desc { font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--muted-light); line-height: 1.6; }

 .gamp-reset {
 font-size: 0.75rem;
 font-family: var(--mono);
 color: var(--muted);
 background: none;
 border: 1px solid var(--border-dim);
 border-radius: 5px;
 padding: 0.3rem 0.7rem;
 cursor: pointer;
 align-self: flex-start;
 }

 .gamp-reset:hover { color: var(--accent); border-color: var(--accent); }

 .hidden { display: none !important; }

 /* Validation deliverables */
 .vd-type-btns {
 display: flex;
 flex-wrap: wrap;
 gap: 0.4rem;
 margin-bottom: 1rem;
 }

 .vd-type-btn {
 font-size: 0.75rem;
 font-family: var(--mono);
 padding: 0.35rem 0.8rem;
 border: 1px solid var(--border);
 border-radius: 6px;
 background: var(--surface2);
 color: var(--muted-light);
 cursor: pointer;
 transition: all 0.15s;
 }

 .vd-type-btn.active, .vd-type-btn:hover {
 border-color: var(--accent);
 color: var(--accent);
 background: var(--accent-glow);
 }

